[Because there is no mention of this being an imported case,
presumably the infection was locally acquired, as apparently were
dengue viral infections that were occurring in this region as well.
One hopes that the rapid response to the appearance of this case will
preclude an outbreak similar to the chikungunya virus outbreak in
Italy in 2007 that also was transmitted by _Ae. albopictus_ (see
ProMED-mail archive no. 20071210.3980).

An excellent assessment of _Ae. albopictus_-related disease risks,
including maps from the European Center for Disease Control, can be
accessed at
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications/Publications/0905_TER_Development_of_Aedes_Albopictus_Risk_Maps.pdf.

A map of the departments of France can be accessed at
http://www.france-travel-info.com/maps-of-France.html. - Mod.TY]
